' slides still operating in the complex until its last season (2012). The slide complex was demolished before the 2014 season. All water attractions are included with the price of park admission tickets.\n\nFrom 2010 to 2019, ''Splashtown at Darien Lake'' was the name of the water park after ''Barracuda Bay''.\n\nAt the end of the 2019 season it was announced that [[Six flags]] was renaming the water park ''Six Flags Hurricane Harbor''. And also announced a new water slide will be added for the 2020 season.\n\n==List of attractions==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=78%\n|-\n! width=150 | Name\n! Type\n! Opened\n! width=80 | Status\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Description\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Ref(s)\n|-\n| Big Kahuna\n| ProSlide Mammoth\n| align=center | 2006\n| {{yes|Operating}}\n| Family sized tube slide located on the edge of Elk Lake. This was relocated from [[Six Flags AstroWorld]].\n| align=center |\n|-\n| Brain Drain\n| ProSlide SkyBox\n| align=center | 2015\n| {{yes|Operating}}\n| 70-foot-high waterslide that sends riders on a 38-foot-per-second free fall\n| align=center |<ref>{{cite news|last=Christmann|first=Samantha|date=February 12, 2015|url=http://www.buffalonews.com/business/darien-lake-doubling-down-on-thrills-20150212|title=Darien Lake doubling down on thrills|newspaper=The Buffalo News|accessdate=February 17, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{nowrap|Cannon Ball Run}}\n| ProSlide CannonBowl\n| align=center | 2010\n| {{yes|Operating}}\n| A standard ProSlide CannonBowl slide in Swirl City.\n| align=center |\n|-\n| Crocodile Isle\n| Wave Pool\n| align=center | 1997\n| {{yes|Operating}}\n| A large family wave pool located past Hook's Lagoon where Adventure Land for Kids used to be.\n| align=center |\n|-\n| Flotation Station\n| Lazy River\n| align=center | 2010\n| {{yes|Operating}}\n| Basic Lazy River south of the Swirl City complex.\n| align=center |\n|-\n| Hook's Lagoon\n| Water Playground\n| align=center | 1996\n| {{yes|Operating}}\n| Five story tall water